  "prompt": "How many questions are asked on Quora each minute on average?",
  "response": "As of the latest available information, Quora does not publicly disclose the exact number of questions asked on its platform each minute. However, based on historical data and growth trends, we can make an informed estimate.\n\n### Estimated Breakdown:\n- **Daily Questions:** Historically, Quora has seen around **300,000 new questions per day**.\n- **Hourly Average:** This translates to approximately **12,500 new questions each hour**.\n- **Minute Average:** Breaking it down further, that's roughly **208 new questions every hour**, or about **3-4 questions per minute**.\n\n### Factors to Consider:\n- **Growth Trends:** Quora's user base has been steadily growing, which could mean an increase in the number of questions asked over time.\n- **User Engagement:** The level of user engagement, including active participation from both question askers and answerers, can influence these numbers.\n- **Content Quality:** Quora emphasizes high-quality, well-thought-out questions, which might affect the volume compared to other platforms.\n\n### Conclusion:\nWhile the estimated average is around **3-4 new questions per minute**, it's important to note that this figure can fluctuate based on various factors such as time of day, global events, and changes in user behavior. For the most accurate and up-to-date statistics, you might consider reaching out directly to Quora's support or checking their official blog and press releases.",
